Yes,since you  use `StartActivityForResult` from  page `activity_main `, then the `OnActivityResult` of `activity_main` will always been executed when you come back from `activity_list`. 

According to your description,you can use the `resultCode` to judge whether you called the function `SetResult` or not. If you call `SetResult` with parameter `Result.Ok`,then we can pass value to page `activity_main `,if not the value `Result.Ok`, that&#39;s the other conditions.

Besides, you can also define a valarible `haveGetData` to identify if you need to pass data to `activity_main`.

For example:

in page `activity_main`

    protected override void OnActivityResult(int requestCode, [GeneratedEnum] Result resultCode, Intent data)
        {
            base.OnActivityResult(requestCode, resultCode, data);
            if (requestCode == 0x001 ) {
                if (resultCode == Result.Ok)
                {
                    string result = data.GetStringExtra(&quot;test&quot;);
                    Log.Debug(&quot;123456&quot;, &quot;******result = &quot; + result);
                }
                else {
                    Log.Debug(&quot;123456&quot;, &quot;******cancel = null &quot;);
                }
            }
        }

in page `activity_list`


    //here define a bool value to flag if you need to pass data to page `activity_main`
     bool haveGetData = false;

     public override void OnBackPressed()
        {
            //base.OnBackPressed();
            haveGetData = true;
            if (haveGetData)
            {
                var intent = new Intent();
                intent.PutExtra(&quot;test&quot;, &quot;nicole..123&quot;);
                SetResult(Result.Ok, intent);
                Finish();
            }
            else {
                var intent = new Intent();
                SetResult(Result.Canceled, intent);
                Finish();
            }
        }

